# PRONUNCIATION

In reading Hawaiian words do not end a syllable with a consonant, and
pronounce all vowels as if they were Italian or French.

 

<div align="center">

|     |     |              |
|-----|-----|--------------|
| a   | =   | a in father. |
| e   | =   | e in they.   |
| i   | =   | i in pin.    |
| o   | =   | o in hold.   |
| u   | =   | oo in spoon. |

</div>

 

This is a fairly good rule for the pronunciation of all Polynesian
words.

 

